<i>noun</i>: 환심 [환심], 허락 [허락], 허가 [허가], 찬동 [찬ː동], 재가 [재가], 인허 [인허], 인준 [인준], 인가 [인가], 용인 [용인], 승인 [승인], 승낙 [승낙], 동의 [동의/동이], 결재 [결째], 가결 [가ː결], 가 [가ː] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>환심 [환심]</dt><br>
<dd>favor; grace; approval</dd><br>
<dd>기쁘고 즐거운 마음.</dd><br>
<dd>A feeling of happiness and joy toward another.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>허락 [허락]</dt><br>
<dd>approval; consent; permission</dd><br>
<dd>요청하는 일을 하도록 들어줌.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of accepting another's request.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>허가 [허가]</dt><br>
<dd>1. permission; approval</dd><br>
<dd>행동이나 일을 할 수 있게 허락함.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of allowing someone to perform a certain act or task.</dd><br>
<dd>2. permission; authorization</dd><br>
<dd>법에 의해 금지되어 있는 행위를 특정한 경우에 한해 허용하여 이를 행할 수 있게 함.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of allowing someone to perform certain acts forbidden by law, only in certain special cases.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>찬동 [찬ː동]</dt><br>
<dd>approval; support</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 행동이나 의견에 찬성하여 뜻을 같이함.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of identifying oneself with a certain movement or opinion and acting on it together with others.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>재가 [재가]</dt><br>
<dd>approval</dd><br>
<dd>아랫사람이 제출한 안건을 윗사람이 결재하여 허가함.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of a superior accepting and authorizing a plan submitted by his/her subordinate.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>인허 [인허]</dt><br>
<dd>authorization; permission; approval</dd><br>
<dd>인정하여 허가함.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of recognizing and permitting something.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>인준 [인준]</dt><br>
<dd>approval; ratification</dd><br>
<dd>결정이나 결과 등을 정식으로 인정하는 일.</dd><br>
<dd>An official recognition of a decision, result, etc.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>인가 [인가]</dt><br>
<dd>authorization; permission; approval</dd><br>
<dd>인정하여 허가함.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of giving an official permission to someone.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>용인 [용인]</dt><br>
<dd>admission; approval; acceptance</dd><br>
<dd>너그러운 마음으로 받아들여 인정함.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of tolerating something with a generous mind.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>승인 [승인]</dt><br>
<dd>1. approval</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일을 허락함.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of agreeing to do something.</dd><br>
<dd>2. acknowledgment</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 사실을 인정함.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of admitting the truth of a fact.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>승낙 [승낙]</dt><br>
<dd>approval; consent; permission</dd><br>
<dd>남이 부탁하는 것을 들어줌.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of accepting another's request.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>동의 [동의/동이]</dt><br>
<dd>1. synonymy; synonymity</dd><br>
<dd>같은 의미.</dd><br>
<dd>The same meaning.</dd><br>
<dd>2. synonymy; synonymity</dd><br>
<dd>같은 의견을 가짐.</dd><br>
<dd>The state of having the same meaning.</dd><br>
<dd>3. approval; permission</dd><br>
<dd>다른 사람의 행위를 승인함.</dd><br>
<dd>An approval on another person's action.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>결재 [결째]</dt><br>
<dd>approval; authorization</dd><br>
<dd>업무를 결정할 권한이 있는 윗사람이 아랫사람이 낸 안건을 허가하거나 승인함.</dd><br>
<dd>The approval of a superior, who is authorized to decide, about a plan submitted by a subordinate.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>가결 [가ː결]</dt><br>
<dd>passage; approval</dd><br>
<dd>회의에 제출된 안건을 좋다고 인정하여 결정함.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of deciding to approve an agenda item that was submitted to a meeting because it is deemed good.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>가 [가ː]</dt><br>
<dd>1. yes; pros; approval</dd><br>
<dd>회의 등에서 어떤 안건에 대해 표결을 할 때 찬성한다는 표시.</dd><br>
<dd>An expression indicating one's agreement when voting for a certain proposal, as in a meeting.</dd><br>
<dd>2. F mark; the lowest grade</dd><br>
<dd>성적이나 등급을 나타내는 ‘수’, ‘우’, ‘미’, ‘양’, ‘가’의 다섯 단계 중에서 가장 낮은 등급.</dd><br>
<dd>The lowest mark when grades are divided into five categories (su, wu, mi, yang, and ga) in the grading system in Korean secondary schools.</dd><br>
<dd>3. be allowed</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 행동이 가능하거나 허용됨.</dd><br>
<dd>The state in which a certain act is possible or allowed.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>